quran[29]{c,v,t}:
  70,11,"They will be seeing them; the guilty will wish if only he could redeem himself from the punishment of that day, by offering his sons."
  70,12,"And his wife and his brother."
  70,13,"And the family in which he was."
  70,14,"And all those who are in the earth – then only if the redemption saves him!"
  70,15,"Never! That is indeed a blazing fire."
  70,16,"A fire that melts the hide."
  70,17,"It calls out to him who reverted and turned away."
  70,18,"And accumulated wealth and hoarded it."
  70,19,"Indeed man is created very impatient, greedy."
  70,20,"Very nervous when touched by misfortune."
  70,21,"And refraining, when good reaches him."
  70,22,"Except those who establish prayer."
  70,23,"Those who are regular in their prayers."
  70,24,"And those in whose wealth exists a recognised right,"
  70,25,"For those who beg, and for the needy who cannot even ask."
  70,26,"And those who believe the Day of Judgement to be true."
  70,27,"And those who fear the punishment of their Lord."
  70,28,"Indeed the punishment of their Lord is not a thing to be unafraid of!"
  70,29,"And those who protect their private organs (from adultery)."
  70,30,"Except with their wives and the bondwomen in their possession, for there is no reproach on them."
  70,31,"So those who desire more than this – it is they who are the transgressors."
  70,32,"And those who protect the property entrusted to them, and their agreements."
  70,33,"And those who are firm upon their testimonies."
  70,34,"And those who protect their prayers."
  70,35,"It is these who will be honoured in Gardens."
  70,36,"So what is the matter with these disbelievers, that they stare at you (O dear Prophet Mohammed – peace and blessings be upon him)?"
  70,37,"From the right and the left, in groups?"
  70,38,"Does every man among them aspire to be admitted into the Garden of serenity?"
  70,39,"Never! We have indeed created them from a thing they know."
